  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Identification and redressal of GBV in refugee and host populations through community-based mechanisms</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to address life-saving needs of GBV survivors in COVID 19-affected areas and provide livelihood support. This UNWOMEN project provides 25 community outreach groups, awareness-raising sessions, FGDs and GBV counselling sessions to refugee and host populations, dignity kits to 2,500 women, and 160 care packages and dignity kits to People with Disabilities (PWD). The project provides life-saving assistance to 16,000 people, including 6,000 women, 2,000 men, 8,000 children, and 320 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
